sonreview.com/?p=18252#.XAmezS3MxQJ The Hudson Review]''. Autumn 2018.\n*\"The Great Interruption: The Story of a Famous Story of Old Port William and How It Ceased to be Told (1935-1978)\" ''The Threepenny Review''. Fall 2018. (A discussion of this story can be found on [https://www.frontporchrepublic.com/2019/11/two-great-interruptions/ Front Porch Republic].)\n\n===Nonfiction===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Title !! Year !! Publisher !! Reprinted/Revised !! ISBN !! scope=\"Col\" class=\"unsortable\"|Notes\n|-\n|''The Long-Legged House''||1969||Harcourt, Brace, Jovanovich; New York||Shoemaker & Hoard (2004), [[Counterpoint (publisher)|Counterpoint]] (2012)||{{ISBNT|1619020017}} (2012)||\n|-\n|''The Hidden Wound''||1970||Houghton Mifflin||Counterpoint (2010)||{{ISBNT|1582434867}}||\n|-\n|''The Unforeseen Wilderness: Kentucky's Red River Gorge''||1971||University Press of Kentucky; Lexington||North Point (1991), Shoemaker & Hoard (2006)||{{ISBNT|1593760922}}||Photographs by Ralph Eugene Meatyard\n|-\n|''A Continuous Harmony: Essays Cultural & Agricultural''||1972||Harcourt, Brace; New York||Shoemaker & Hoard (2004), Counterpoint (2012)||{{ISBNT|1593760922}}||\n|-\n|''The Unsettling of America: Culture and Agriculture''||1977||Sierra Club, San Francisco||Avon Books (1978), Sierra Club/Counterpoint (third edition, 1996)||{{ISBNT|0871568772}}||\n|-\n|''The Gift of Good Land: Further Essays Cultural and Agricultural''||1981||North Point, San Francisco||Counterpoint (2009)||{{ISBNT|1582434840}}||\n|-\n| ''Recollected Essays: 1965\u20131980''||1981||North Point, San Francisco||||{{ISBNT|086547026X}}||\n|-\n|''Standing by Words''||1983||North Point, San Francisco||Shoemaker & Hoard (2005), Counterpoint (2011)||{{ISBNT|1582437459}}||\n|-\n|''Meeting the Expectations of the Land: Essays in Sustainable Agriculture and Stewardship''||1986||North Point, San Francisco||||{{ISBNT|086547172X}}||Editor with Wes Jackson and Bruce Colman\n|-\n|''Home Economics: Fourteen Essays''||1987||North Point, San Francisco||Counterpoint (2009)||{{ISBNT|1582434859}}||\n|-\n|''Descendants and Ancestors of Captain James W. Berry''||1990||Hub, Bowling Green, KY||||||With Laura Berry\n|-\n|''[[Harlan Hubbard]]: Life and Work''||1990||University Press of Kentucky||||{{ISBNT|0813109426}}||\n|-\n|''What Are People For?''||1990||North Point, San Francisco||Counterpoint (2010)||{{ISBNT|1582434875}}||\n|-\n|''Standing on Earth: Selected Essays''||1991||Golgonooza Press, UK||||{{ISBNT|0903880466}}||\n|-\n|''Sex, Economy, Freedom & Community''||1992||Pantheon, New York||||{{ISBNT|0679756515}}||\n|-\n|''[https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1640090959/ref=dbs_a_def_rwt_hsch_vapi_thcv_p1_i1 The Farm]''||1995||[[Gray Zeitz]] ([[Larkspur Press]], Monterey, Kentucky)||Counterpoint (2018) ||{{ISBNT|9781640090958}} (2018)||\n|-\n|''Another Turn of the Crank''||1996||Counterpoint, Washington, DC||||{{ISBNT|1887178287}}||\n|-\n|''Grace: Photographs of Rural America''||2000||Safe Harbor Books, New London, NH||||{{ISBNT|0966579836}}||Photographs by [[Gregory Spaid]], essay by [[Gene Logsdon]], story by Wendell Berry\n|-\n|''Life Is a Miracle''||2000||Counterpoint, Washington, DC||||{{ISBNT|1582431418}}||\n|-\n|''In the Presence of Fear: Three Essays for a Changed World''||2001||Orion, Great Barrington, MA||||{{ISBNT|0913098604}}||\n|-\n|''The Art of the Commonplace: The Agrarian Essays of Wendell Berry''||2002||Counterpoint, Washington, DC||||{{ISBNT|1582431469}}||\n|-\n|''Citizens Dissent: Security, Morality, and Leadership in an Age of Terror''||2003||Orion, Great Barrington, MA||||{{ISBNT|0913098620}}||With [[David James Duncan]]. Foreword by Laurie Lane-Zucker\n|-\n|''Citizenship Papers''||2003||Shoemaker & Hoard, Washington, DC||Counterpoint (2014)||{{ISBNT|1619024470}}||\n|-\n|''Tobacco Harvest: An Elegy''||2004||University Press of Kentucky, Lexington, KY||||{{ISBNT|0813123275}}||Photographs by [[James Baker Hall]]\n|-\n|''Blessed Are the Peacemakers: Christ's Teac