ition (with the added short story and engravings) of the 2014 Larkspur Press edition, based on the 1995 West Meadow Press portfolio.\n|-\n|''Sabbaths 2016''||2018||Larkspur, Monterey, KY||||||\"What Passes, What Remans\" (2016, VIII) is also to be found in ''The Art of Loading Brush''. Wood engravings by Wesley Bates.\n|}\n\n===Interviews===\n*Beattie, L. Elisabeth (Editor). \"Wendell Berry\" in ''Conversations With Kentucky Writers'',  University Press of Kentucky, 1996.\n*Berger, Rose Marie. \"Wendell Berry interview complete text,\" ''Sojourner's Magazine'', July 2004 <ref>{{cite web|url=https://sojo.net/magazine/july-2004/web-exclusive-wendell-berry-interview-complete-text|title=Web Exclusive: Wendell Berry interview complete text, Sojourners Magazine/July 2004|publisher=Sojo.net|date=|accessdate=August 1, 2015}}</ref>\n*DeChristopher, Tim. \"To Live and Love with a Dying World: A conversation between Tim DeCristopher and Wendell Berry\". ''Orion'', Spring 2020.\n*Fisher-Smith, Jordan. \"Field Observations: An Interview with Wendell Berry'\" <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thesunmagazine.org/issues/218/field-observations|title=Field Observations|publisher=The Sun Magazine|date=|accessdate=December 21, 2017 }}</ref>\n*Grubbs, Morris Allen (Editor). ''Conversations with Wendell Berry'', University Press of Mississippi, 2007. {{ISBN|1578069920}}\n*hooks, bell. \"Healing Talk: A Conversation\" in \"Belonging: A Culture of Place\", 2009, Routledge. \n*Lehrer, Brian. ''The Brian Lehrer Show'' WYNC, October 17, 2013 <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wnyc.org/story/wendell-berry/|title=Wendell Berry|publisher=WNYC.org|date=October 17, 2013|accessdate=November 2, 2013}}</ref>\n*Leonard, Sarah. \"Nature as an Ally\" ''Dissent'', Vol. 59, No. 2, Spring, 2012\n*Minick, Jim. \"A Citizen and a Native: An Interview with Wendell Berry\" ''Appalachian Journal'', Vol. 31, Nos 3\u20134, (Spring-Summer, 2004)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nantahalareview.org/issue3-1/view/Minick.htm|title